# 3. PROFINET — Deep Dive

# 3.1 What is PROFINET?

PROFINET stands for:

> **PROcess FIeld NETwork**

It is Industrial Ethernet for automation systems.

Uses:

* Standard Ethernet hardware
* TCP/IP
* Real-time communication
* High-speed motion control

---

# 3.2 Why PROFINET Replaced PROFIBUS

Industrial automation needed:

* Higher speed
* Ethernet integration
* IT connectivity
* Large data transfer
* Motion synchronization
* Flexible topologies

PROFINET solved these limitations.

---

# 3.3 PROFINET Architecture

```text
             +------------------+
             |   PLC / IO Ctrl  |
             +------------------+
                    |
          Industrial Ethernet Switch
         /            |            \
        /             |             \
 +---------+     +---------+    +---------+
 | IO Dev1 |     | Drive   |    | HMI     |
 +---------+     +---------+    +---------+
```

---

# 3.4 PROFINET Device Roles

## A. IO Controller

Usually PLC.

Controls communication.

---

## B. IO Device

Field devices:

* Remote I/O
* Drives
* Sensors

---

## C. IO Supervisor

Engineering station:

* Programming
* Diagnostics
* Monitoring

---

# 3.5 PROFINET Communication Channels

PROFINET uses multiple communication methods simultaneously.

---

## A. Standard TCP/IP Communication

Used for:

* Programming
* Diagnostics
* Web servers
* SCADA

Non-real-time.

---

## B. RT (Real Time)

For normal industrial I/O communication.

Typical update:

* 1–10 ms

---

## C. IRT (Isochronous Real Time)

Ultra-fast deterministic communication.

Used for:

* Servo drives
* Motion control
* Robotics

Update times:

* <1 ms

---

# 3.6 PROFINET Communication Stack

```text
Application Layer
-------------------
PROFINET Protocol
-------------------
Ethernet MAC
-------------------
Physical Layer
```

---

# 3.7 PROFINET Real-Time Concept

Normal Ethernet has:

* Collisions
* Variable delays
* Non-deterministic traffic

PROFINET modifies Ethernet behavior.

---

## RT Mechanism

RT frames bypass TCP/IP stack.

```text
Application -> Ethernet directly
```

Result:

* Faster communication
* Lower latency

---

## IRT Mechanism

IRT reserves bandwidth/time slots.

```text
Time Slot 1 -> Servo 1
Time Slot 2 -> Servo 2
Time Slot 3 -> IO
```

This creates deterministic synchronization.

---

# 3.8 PROFINET Topologies

## A. Star

```text
        Switch
      /   |   \
     A    B    C
```

Most common.

---

## B. Line

```text
PLC -> Device1 -> Device2 -> Device3
```

Uses integrated switch ports.

---

## C. Ring

Supports redundancy.

```text
A -> B -> C -> A
```

---

## D. Tree

Combination topology.

---

# 3.9 PROFINET Physical Layer

Uses:

* CAT5e/CAT6
* Fiber optic
* RJ45 or M12 connectors

Speeds:

* 100 Mbps
* 1 Gbps

---

# 3.10 PROFINET Device Discovery

