# 25. LLDP Frames

Used for topology discovery.

Switches/devices exchange:

* Port info
* Neighbor info

Enables:

* Automatic topology mapping

---

# 26. Alarm Frames

PROFINET alarms use dedicated frame IDs.

Examples:

* Module removed
* Overtemperature
* Short circuit

Alarms are prioritized.

---

# 27. PROFINET Frame Timing

Critical for real-time systems.

---

# 27.1 Cycle Time

Can be:

```text
250 us
500 us
1 ms
4 ms
```

Depends on application.

---

# 27.2 Jitter

Variation in frame timing.

Low jitter required for:

* Servo drives
* Robotics

---

# 28. Cut-Through Switching

Many PROFINET switches use:

* Cut-through forwarding

Switch forwards frame before fully receiving it.

Result:

* Extremely low latency

---

# 29. Store-and-Forward vs Cut-Through

| Method          | Latency |
| --------------- | ------- |
| Store & Forward | Higher  |
| Cut Through     | Lower   |

IRT often uses cut-through.

